.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBgetOldSelection(This) -> integer() when This :: wxBookCtrlEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the page that was selected before the change, \fIwxNOT\\_FOUND\fR if none was selected.


.RE
.B
\fBgetSelection(This) -> integer() when This :: wxBookCtrlEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the currently selected page, or \fIwxNOT\\_FOUND\fR if none was selected.

.PP
Note: under Windows, \fIgetSelection/1\fR will return the same value as \fIgetOldSelection/1\fR when called from the \fIEVT_BOOKCTRL_PAGE_CHANGING\fR handler and not the page which is going to be selected.


.RE
.B
\fBsetOldSelection(This, Page) -> ok\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             This :: wxBookCtrlEvent(),\fR
\fB                             Page :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the id of the page selected before the change.


.RE
.B
\fBsetSelection(This, Page) -> ok\fR
\fB                      when This :: wxBookCtrlEvent(), Page :: integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the selection member variable.


.RE
